race.comment: ZOUSOUTH (6) showed good early speed and fought on beaten 1L resuming over 1114m at this track. Has a low barrier and should be all the favours in running. In a top metro barn and is sure to keep improving. BUTTERCUP (7) has been nudged out her last three and was heavily supported at Camperdown last time. Meech stays aboard and will likely push forward. Has claims with average luck in running. SHAHAR (10) was only beaten 2.4L in an Open 2 at Sandown before spelling. Resumed as favourite at Cranbourne with Meech in the saddle and pulled up with an issue. From an inside gate she's likely to lead/ box seat and quick improvement is on the cards. DISCREET POINT (3) went close here first-up and showed enough in her maiden preparation to consider. The gate is awkward but he keeps John Allen.
